etherEntry.name: etherEntry
etherEntry.description: Generic status and parameter values for an Ethernet interface.

etherIndex.name: etherIndex
etherIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an Ethernet interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

etherAlignmentErrors.name: etherAlignmentErrors
etherAlignmentErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that are not an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check.

etherFCSErrors.name: etherFCSErrors
etherFCSErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that are an integral number of octets in length that do not pass the FCS check.

etherTxTable.name: etherTxTable
etherTxTable.description: A list of Ethernet transmit entries.

etherTxEntry.name: etherTxEntry
etherTxEntry.description: Transmit status and parameter values for an Ethernet interface.

etherTxIndex.name: etherTxIndex
etherTxIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an Ethernet interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

etherTxSingleCollisionFrames.name: etherTxSingleCollisionFrames
etherTxSingleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by exactly one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts or ifOutNUcastPkts object and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the etherTxMultipleCollisionFrames object.

etherTxMultipleCollisionFrames.name: etherTxMultipleCollisionFrames
etherTxMultipleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts or ifOutNUcastPkts object and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the etherTxSingleCollisionFrames object.

etherMulticastEntry.name: etherMulticastEntry
etherMulticastEntry.description: EtherMulticast status and parameter values for an Ethernet interface.

etherMulticastIndex.name: etherMulticastIndex
etherMulticastIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an Ethernet interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

etherMulticastBytesIn.name: etherMulticastBytesIn
etherMulticastBytesIn.description: A count of frames successfully received on a particular interface and for which the destination address multicast bit was set. Bytes that are counted by an instance of this object are also counted by the corresponding instance of the ifInOctets object.

etherMulticastBytesOut.name: etherMulticastBytesOut
etherMulticastBytesOut.description: A count of successfully frames successfully transmitted on a particular interface and for which the destination address multicast bit was set. Bytes that are counted by an instance of this object are also counted by the corresponding instance of the ifOutOctets object.

etherXTxTable.name: etherXTxTable
etherXTxTable.description: A list of Ethernet extended transmit entries.

etherXTxEntry.name: etherXTxEntry
etherXTxEntry.description: Extended transmit status and parameter values for an Ethernet interface.

etherXTxIndex.name: etherXTxIndex
etherXTxIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an Ethernet interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

etherXTxExcessiveCollisions.name: etherXTxExcessiveCollisions
etherXTxExcessiveCollisions.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular interface fails due to excessive collisions.
